article.headline: St. Bonaventure 68, Ark.-Little Rock 55
article.story: LITTLE ROCK, Ark. -- Demetrius Conger had 21 points and 10 rebounds Wednesday as St. Bonaventure defeated Arkansas-Little Rock for the second time this season, 68-55. Ogo Adegboye added 17 points and nine assists for the Bonnies (8-5), who also beat the Trojans 77-64 on Nov. 14. Da'Quan Cook and Andrew Nicholson scored 11 points each for St. Bonaventure. Daylon Guy had 14 points and five assists for Little Rock (8-9), which has lost three straight games and six of its last eight. Solomon Bozeman added 13 points and Courtney Jackson had 10. The teams were tied at 26 before the Bonnies opened the second half on a 12-3 run. Bozeman hit back-to-back 3-pointers to bring Little Rock within 39-37 with 12:59 remaining, but St. Bonaventure answered with a 16-2 run that featured seven points from Conger and back-to-back 3-pointers from Adegboye to put the Bonnies ahead 55-39.
